author: @a.r.3767
text:
Let's try to connect some of the dots here (gosh, there are many):
- Taeyong asked why Mark was so late. Since everyone's dream was synchronized, I guess we can say that Johnny was texting Mark in Stage 3, hence the question, "Is everything okay?"
- Jaemin broke his whistle in Stage 3 and woke up from his dream. Could it be that he was connected to Mark, hence the interrupted sleep and Mark coming late to Kwangya?
- Jeno had a feeling that he would meet Jungwoo. He was playing with the water in the pond exactly the same way Taeil did in the pool in Stage 2. In a way, I think Jeno was connected to Taeil, while Jungwoo was connected to Ten (the connection obviously didn't stop there).
- If this was Sungtaro's first time in what Jaehyun called "Kwangya of unconsciousness", timeline-wise, this video could've taken place sometime before the Resonance era. Are we looking at the past now? Is this what Ether was all about? After all, it connects "dimension to dimension, people within people..."

Might add more later when I have the brain cells to spare lmao.
